20#include "Point.h"
21#include "Quadrilateral.h"
22
23#include <array>
24
25namespace ZXing {
26
27/**
28* <p>This class implements a perspective transform in two dimensions. Given four source and four
29* destination points, it will compute the transformation implied between them. The code is based
30* directly upon section 3.4.2 of George Wolberg's "Digital Image Warping"; see pages 54-56.</p>
31*/
32class PerspectiveTransform
33{
34 using value_t = PointF::value_t;
35 value_t a11, a12, a13, a21, a22, a23, a31, a32, a33;
36 bool _isValid = false;
37
38 PerspectiveTransform(value_t a11, value_t a21, value_t a31, value_t a12, value_t a22, value_t a32, value_t a13,
39 value_t a23, value_t a33)
40 : a11(a11), a12(a12), a13(a13), a21(a21), a22(a22), a23(a23), a31(a31), a32(a32), a33(a33), _isValid(true)
41 {}
42
43 PerspectiveTransform inverse() const;
44 PerspectiveTransform times(const PerspectiveTransform& other) const;
45
46 static PerspectiveTransform UnitSquareTo(const QuadrilateralF& q);
47
48public:
49 PerspectiveTransform(const QuadrilateralF& src, const QuadrilateralF& dst);
50
51 PointF operator()(PointF p) const;
52
53 bool isValid() const { return _isValid; }
54};
55
56} // ZXing
